	,"x4freetext":[" Charged particles were identified"
		,"in focal plane of the spectrograph by telescope"
		,"consisting of isobutane-filled ion chamber with two"
		,"proportional-counters, serving as dE detector and"
		,"a planar plastic scintillator detector which measured"
		,"the total energy E deposited by particles passing"
		,"through the ion chamber."]
	}
      ]
     ,"SAMPLE":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	 ,"x4code":null
	,"x4freetext":["The beam was delivered to a natural Cr target of"
		,"thickness 300 microg/cm2 on a 20 microg/cm2 carbon"
		,"backing that was mounted in the target chamber of the"
		,"spectrograph. The natural abundance of 52Cr is 84%."]
	}
      ]
     ,"METHOD":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	 ,"x4codes":[{"code":"EDE", "dict":"METHOD", "idict":21,"hlp":"Particle identification by `E/Delta E` measurement"}]
	,"x4freetext":[" The Super-Enge Split-Pole Spectrograph, which"
		,"accepted a solid angle of 4.6 msr, was rotated from"
		,"scattering angles of 15 to 50 degrees at increments"
		,"of 5 degree to measure angular distributions of"
		,"protons from the 52Cr(d,p)53Cr reaction."]
	}
      ]
